.TH "of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_name" 9 "of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_name \- assign named reserved memory region to given device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_name
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to the device to configure
.IP "np" 12
pointer to the device node with 'memory-region' property
.IP "name" 12
name of the selected memory region
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error-code on failure.
